register.description: The GPMC_REVISION register contains the IP revision code.

bitfield.description: IP revision. [[br]]Major revision is [[br]][7:4]. [[br]]Minor revision is [[br]][3:0]. [[br]]Examples: 10h for revision 1.0, 21h for revision 2.1.

register.description: The GPMC_SYSCONFIG register controls the various parameters of the OCP interface.

bitenum.description: Smart-idle. Acknowledgment to an idle request is given based on the internal activity of the module
No-idle. An idle request is never acknowledged
Force-idle. An idle request is acknowledged unconditionally

bitfield.description: Software reset (Set 1 to this bit triggers a module reset. [[br]]This bit is automatically reset by hardware. [[br]]During reads, it always returns 0).

bitenum.description: Automatic interface clock gating strategy is applied based on the Interconnect activity.

register.description: The GPMC_SYSSTATUS register provides status information about the module, excluding the interrupt status information.
The GPMC_IRQSTATUS interrupt status register regroups all the status of the module internal events that can generate an interrupt.

bitfield.description: Status of the Wait1 Edge Detection interrupt

bitenum.description: A transition on WAIT1 input pin has been detected
A transition on WAIT1 input pin has not been detected

bitfield.description: Status of the Wait0 Edge Detection interrupt

bitenum.description: A transition on WAIT0 input pin has been detected
A transition on WAIT0 input pin has not been detected
Indicates that CountValue is equal to 0
Indicates than at least GPMC_PREFETCH_STATUS[16] FIFOTHRESHOLDSTATUS bytes are available in prefetch mode and at least FIFOTHRESHOLD bytes free places are available in write-posting mode.
Indicates than less than GPMC_PREFETCH_STATUS[16] FIFOTHRESHOLDSTATUS bytes are available in prefetch mode and less than FIFOTHRESHOLD bytes free places are available in write-posting mode.

register.description: The GPMC_IRQENABLE interrupt enable register allows to mask/unmask the module internal sources of interrupt, on a event-by-event basis.

bitfield.description: Enables the Wait1 Edge Detection interrupt

bitenum.description: Wait1EdgeDetection event generates an interrupt if occurs

bitfield.description: Enables the Wait0 Edge Detection interrupt

bitenum.description: Wait0EdgeDetection event generates an interrupt if occurs

bitfield.description: Enables TerminalCountEvent interrupt issuing in pre-fetch or write posting mode

register.description: The GPMC_TIMEOUT_CONTROL register allows the user to set the start value of the timeout counter

bitfield.description: Start value of the time-out counter (000 corresponds to 0 GPMC.FCLK cycle, 1h corresponds to 1 GPMC.FCLK cycle, and 1FFh corresponds to 511 GPMC.FCLK cycles)
Enable bit of the TimeOut feature

register.description: The GPMC_ERR_ADDRESS register stores the address of the illegal access when an error occurs.

bitfield.description: Address of illegal access: A30 (0 for memory region, 1 for GPMC register region) and A29 to A0 (1GByte maximum)

register.description: The GPMC_ERR_TYPE register stores the type of error when an error occurs.

bitfield.description: System Command of the transaction that caused the error

bitenum.description: The error is due to a non supported Address
The error is due to a non supported Command
The error is due to a time out

bitfield.description: Error validity status - Must be explicitly cleared with a write 1 transaction

bitenum.description: Error detected and logged in the other error fields
All error fields no longer valid

register.description: The configuration register allows global configuration of the GPMC.

bitfield.description: Selects the polarity of input pin WAIT1.
Selects the polarity of input pin WAIT0.
Controls the WP output pin level.

bitenum.description: A26-A11 are not modified during an external memory access.
No effect. GPMC controls all addresses.

register.description: The status register provides global status bits of the GPMC.

bitfield.description: Is a copy of input pin WAIT1. [[br]](Reset value is WAIT1 input pin sampled at IC reset)
Is a copy of input pin WAIT0. [[br]](Reset value is WAIT0 input pin sampled at IC reset)
Stores the empty status of the write buffer
Define the number of GPMC.FCLK cycles to be substracted from RdCycleTime, WrCycleTime, AccessTime, CSRdOffTime, CSWrOffTime, ADVRdOffTime, ADVWrOffTime, OEOffTime, WEOffTime
Selects the CS (active low) where Prefetch Postwrite engine is active
Selects the number of bytes to be read or written by the engine to the selected CS (active low)
Resets the FIFO pointer and starts the engine

bitenum.description: Resets the FIFO pointer to 0 in prefetch mode and 40h in postwrite mode and starts the engine
64 bytes available to be read or 64 empty places to be written
0 byte available to be read or 0 free empty place to be written

bitfield.description: Set when FIFOPointer exceeds FIFOThreshold value.

bitenum.description: FIFOPointer greater than FIFOThreshold. Writing to this bit has no effect
FIFOPointer smaller or equal to FIFOThreshold. Writing to this bit has no effect

bitfield.description: Number of remaining bytes to be read or to be written by the engine according to the TransferCount value.

bitenum.description: 8 Kbytes remaining to be read or to be written
1 byte remaining to be read or to be writte
0 byte remaining to be read or to be written
